802d8c01-07c2-49e0-a085-c4c57ce0c97f.1e708abb-c896-46a7-98d2-0c8535f54285.description=
This flow authenticates against a keystone identity service, and returns an authentication token and a list of endpoints available to the specified user. 

This flow should handle authentication against public/private cloud systems installed using the default procedure outlined in the OpenStack administrators guide, as well as
the HP cloud services public cloud. 

Note\: There are two endpoints returned by this flow, cdnEndpoint and blockStorageEndpoint, which are HP plugin extensions to OpenStack, and these two outputs will
be empty if this flow is run against a generic Keystone implementation. 

Inputs\:
    identityServiceEndpoint - The identity service endpoint to use for the authentication request. 
Example\: https\://region-a.geo-1.identity.hpcloudsvc.com\:35357/v2.0
    identityServiceUsername - Username to supply to keystone for authentication
Examples\: admin, user@somedomain.com
    identityServicePassword - Password to supply to keystone for authentication
Example\: somepassword
    tenantId - The ID of the keystone tenant to authenticate against. This is usually an integer or a unique string identifier, but not the name of the tenant.
Examples\: 123456798, 86aae2e3c911436c986999b8d930c073
    computeRegion - The region of the compute endpoint to select. This region is also used for the image block storage endpoints. 
                                If the region is not specified, the first endpoint in the array of endpoints returned is selected. 
Example\: az-2.region-a.geo-1
    objectStorageRegion - The region of the object storage endpoint to select. This region is also used for the CDN endpoint.
                                If the region is not specified, the first endpoint in the array of endpoints returned is selected. 
Example\: region-a.geo-1
    username - The username to use for authentication to the URL. For NTLM authentication, the required format is domain\user.
    password - The password to use for authentication to the URL.
    authType - The authentication type that this operation uses when trying to execute the request on the target server.
Valid values\: basic, form, digest, ntlm, kerberos, anonymous (no authentication).
Default value\: anonymous - authentication not used when executing the request.
    kerberosConfFile - The path to the Kerberos configuration file. If this input is empty the kdc (Key Distribution Center) and realm will get their values from the full domain name which is obtained from the url of the web server.
    timeout - The number of milliseconds to wait for a connection to be established. This input should be assigned a value greater than or equal to zero. A timeout value of zero is an infinite timeout.
Default value\: 0.
    socketTimeout - The number of milliseconds to wait for the data to be retrieved. This input should be assigned a value greater than or equal to zero. A socketTimeout value of zero is an infinite timeout.
Default value\: 0.
    useCookies - If true, enables cookie tracking. Cookies will be stored between consecutive calls. This is a boolean input. If a non-boolean value is specified, it will take the default value.
Default value\: true.
    followRedirects - If true, the GET command automatically follows redirects. This is a boolean input. If a non-boolean value is specified, it will take the default value.
Default value\: false.
    proxy - A proxy to use when accessing the web site.
    proxyPort - The port on the proxy to connect to.
    proxyUsername - The username to use when connecting to the proxy.
    proxyPassword - The password to use when connecting to the proxy.
    encodeURL - If true, automatically encodes the URL. This is a boolean input. If a non-boolean value is specified, it will take the default value.
Default value\: false.
    userAgent - The value that should be used if the HTTP header USER_AGENT has to be overridden.
    characterSet - The character encoding that should be used for the HTTP Get request and response. 
Default value\: UTF-8.
    trustAllRoots - If true, enables weak security over SSL. A SSL certificate is trusted even if no trusted CA issued it.
Default value\: false.
    keystore - URL of the keystore file or local path to it (e.g. %JAVA_HOME%/jre/lib/security/cacerts). It may be empty if HTTPS client  authentication is not to be used.
    keystorePassword - Password to unlock the keystore.
    trustKeystore - URL of the truststore file or local path to it (e.g. %JAVA_HOME%/jre/lib/security/cacerts). It may be empty if HTTPS server authentication is not to be used.
    trustPassword - Password to unlock the truststore.
    headerNamesList - A list containing the names of headers that should be used for the request.
Example\: Accept,Content-Type
    headerValuesList - A list containing the values of headers that should be used for the request. 
Example\: text/plain,application/x-www-form-urlencoded
    queryNamesList - A list containing the names of query parameters that should be used for the request. 
Example\: parameterName1,parameterName2 
    queryValuesList - A list containing the values of query parameters that should be used for the request. 
Example\: parameterValue1,parameterValue2
    delimiter - A delimiter that separates the elements in the names and values lists.
Default value\:  (carriage return).

Results\:
    authToken - The token needed for subsequent API calls
    computeEndpoint - Endpoint to use for compute (nova) API calls
    imageEndpoint - Endpoint to use for image (glance) API calls
    objectStorageEndpoint - Endpoint to use for object storage (swift) API calls
    cdnEndpoint - Endpoint to use for CDN API calls
    blockStorageEndpoint- Endpoint to use for block storage API calls.
    exception - If an error occurred, the stack trace of the thrown error.

Responses\:
    success - The URL retrieved successfully.
    failure - The URL could not be retrieved.
    unknown - The auth request resulted in an INFORMATIONAL or REDIRECTION code. This usually means the request failed.

Notes\:
See the HTTP Client Get operation for additional notes.

802d8c01-07c2-49e0-a085-c4c57ce0c97f.28f85181-85a1-4842-8da6-d6cf43b7355b.description=
Create a new server instance using a given image and a virtual hardware configuration (flavor). 

User defined metadata can be attached to the new server using the metadata input. The format of the metadata is a JSON Object, 
with name/value pairs for the metadata items

Up to 5 small files (<1kb) can be injected into the server's filesystem at creation time. These files are specified using the personality
input, which is a JSON array of Objects. Each JSON Object contains a property called "path", which is the full path to the file
on the server we are creating, and a property called "contents", which is the contents of the file to create, base64 encoded. There
is an operation under 'Library/Utility Operations/Base64 Encoder' to dynamically encode file contents, if needed. 


Inputs\:
    computeEndpoint - The endpoint to use for the request. 
    authToken - The authentication token to use for the request.
Example\: HPAuth_4f3b5044e4b05c3dbefdee82
    name - Name for the new server. 
Example\: server1
    imageRef - The image reference to use for the server. This can be either an integer id of an image, or a string which is the full URI of the image.
Examples\: 1242, https\://az-1.region-a.geo-1.compute.hpcloudsvc.com/v1.1/28400914814935/images/1242 
    flavorRef - The flavor to use for the new server. This can also be specified as a simple id, or a complete URI.
Examples\: 101, https\://az-1.region-a.geo-1.compute.hpcloudsvc.com/v1.1/16634948504394/flavors/101
    keyName - Name of the security key to use for the new server
Example\: MyKey
    securityGroups - A JSON Array of Objects, each of which describes a security group. A server can be placed in multiple security groups, and the security group 
                               rules from each group are associated to the server. 
Example\: [{"name"\:"group1"},{"name"\:"group2"}]
    adminPassword - The admin password for the server. If this password does not meet the security requirements of the system, the server
                                 may enter an ERROR state, in which case the adminPassword must be changed using the 'Change Server Admin Password' 
                                 operation. There is a bug in OpenStack where this password may just be ignored if it does not meet the requirements,
                                 and a new random password is generated. 
    metadata - A JSON Object which defines name/value pairs of metadata for the new server.
Example\: { "My Server Name" \: "Apache1", "min_ram" \: "2" }
    personality - A JSON Array of Objects, each of which defines a file to inject into the new servers' filesystem. 
Example\: [{ "path" \: "/etc/banner.txt",  "contents" \: "ICAgICAgDQoiQSBjbG91ZCBkb2VzIG5vdCBrbm93IHdoeSBp dCBtb3ZlcyBpbiBqdXN0IHN1Y2ggYSBkaXJlY3Rpb24gYW5k IGF0IHN1Y2ggYSBzcGVlZC4uLkl0IGZlZWxzIGFuIGltcHVs c2lvbi4uLnRoaXMgaXMgdGhlIHBsYWNlIHRvIGdvIG5vdy4g QnV0IHRoZSBza3kga25vd3MgdGhlIHJlYXNvbnMgYW5kIHRo ZSBwYXR0ZXJucyBiZWhpbmQgYWxsIGNsb3VkcywgYW5kIHlv dSB3aWxsIGtub3csIHRvbywgd2hlbiB5b3UgbGlmdCB5b3Vy c2VsZiBoaWdoIGVub3VnaCB0byBzZWUgYmV5b25kIGhvcml6 b25zLiINCg0KLVJpY2hhcmQgQmFjaA\=\="   }]
    username - The username to use for authentication to the URL. For NTLM authentication, the required format is domain\user.
    password - The password to use for authentication to the URL.
    authType - The authentication type that this operation uses when trying to execute the request on the target server.
Valid values\: basic, form, digest, ntlm, kerberos, anonymous (no authentication).
Default value\: anonymous - authentication not used when executing the request.
    kerberosConfFile - The path to the Kerberos configuration file. If this input is empty the kdc (Key Distribution Center) and realm will get their values from the full domain name which is obtained from the url of the web server.
    postDocument - The raw text to be posted by this operation using the HTTP POST method. This does not have to be a path to a file/document on the disk.
    contentType - The content type that should be set in the request header, representing the MIME-type of the data in the message body.
Examples\: "text/html", "text/html; charset\=UTF-8", "application/x-www-form-urlencoded".
    characterSet - The character encoding of the text to be posted. If not specified this will be taken from the 'charset' field that can be specified in the contentType input. If the 'charset' field is absent it will be set to ISO-8859-1 by default.
    timeout - The number of milliseconds to wait for a connection to be established. This input should be assigned a value greater than or equal to zero. A timeout value of zero is an infinite timeout.
Default value\: 0.
    useCookies - If true, enables cookie tracking. Cookies will be stored between consecutive calls. This is a boolean input. If a non-boolean value is specified, it will take the default value.
Default value\: true.
    proxy - The hostname or IP address of a computer that acts as a proxy server.
    proxyPort - The port on the proxy server to connect to.
    proxyUsername - The username to use when connecting to the proxy server.
    proxyPassword - The password to use when connecting to the proxy server.
    encodeURL - If true, automatically encodes the URL. This is a boolean input. If a non-boolean value is specified, it will take the default value.
Default value\: false.
    trustAllRoots - If true, enables weak security over SSL. A SSL certificate is trusted even if no trusted CA issued it.
Default value\: false.
    keystore - URL of the keystore file or local path to it (e.g. %JAVA_HOME%/jre/lib/security/cacerts). It may be empty if HTTPS client  authentication is not to be used.
    keystorePassword - Password to unlock the keystore.
    trustKeystore - URL of the truststore file or local path to it (e.g. %JAVA_HOME%/jre/lib/security/cacerts). It may be empty if HTTPS server authentication is not to be used.
    trustPassword - Password to unlock the truststore.
    headerNamesList - A list containing the names of headers that should be used for the request.
Example\: Accept,Content-Type
    headerValuesList - A list containing the values of headers that should be used for the request. 
Example\: text/plain,application/x-www-form-urlencoded
    queryNamesList - A list containing the names of query parameters that should be used for the request. 
Example\: parameterName1,parameterName2 
    queryValuesList - A list containing the values of query parameters that should be used for the request. 
Example\: parameterValue1,parameterValue2
    delimiter - A delimiter that separates the elements in the names and values lists.
Default value\:  (carriage return).

Results\: 
    serverId - This is the primary output. The ID of the created server.
    serverDetails  - A JSON array of objects describing the created server. When you create a server, only the server ID, links and the admin password are guaranteed to be returned in the request. Additional attributes can be retrieved by performing subsequent 'Get' operations on the server.

Responses\:
    success - The POST command completed.
    failure - The POST operation failed.
    unknown - The POST was not fully processed, the server responded with an informational response or the specified URL has moved.

Notes\:
See the HTTP Client Post Raw operation for Notes.
802d8c01-07c2-49e0-a085-c4c57ce0c97f.619cdf31-3690-480e-bde3-75517af20042.prompt=Enter a value for pnetwork 802d8c01-07c2-49e0-a085-c4c57ce0c97f.7dd49937-1bfc-423a-831d-713e3a1de29d.prompt=Enter a value for zone 802d8c01-07c2-49e0-a085-c4c57ce0c97f.a9423041-5d50-4a86-85ed-ed1f641c133b.description=
Counts from one number to another number.

Inputs\:
from - The number to start counting at
to - The number to count to
incrementBy - The amount to increment by during each count.
reset - If set to true, then the counter will restart counting from the beginning.

Responses\:
has more - Not yet done counting.
failure - Something went wrong.
no more - Done counting. This will only be returned once, then counting restarts.

Returns\:
The number that was just counted.
802d8c01-07c2-49e0-a085-c4c57ce0c97f.bca886d8-56f6-47cf-a38b-cab60651e623.description=
Compares two strings, returning a true response if and only if they contain the same sequence of characters. A null string is considered to be equal to an empty string.

Inputs\:
string1 - The first string.
string2 - The second string.
ignoreCase - If set to 'true', then the comparison ignores case considerations. The two strings are considered equal ignoring case if they are of the same length and corresponding characters in the two strings are equal ignoring case. If set to any value other than 'true', then the strings must match exactly to be considered equal.

responses\:
true - If the two strings are equal
false - If the two strings are not equal
802d8c01-07c2-49e0-a085-c4c57ce0c97f.cbb8972c-3f8c-4cd1-833c-b59ef4a45413.description=
Returns details of the specified account associated server.

Inputs\:
    computeEndpoint - The endpoint to which requests are sent. 
Example\: https\://az-1.region-a.geo-1.compute.hpcloudsvc.com/v1.1/28400914814935
    serverId - The ID of server for which to retrieve the details.
Example\: 55932
    authToken - The authentication token used for the request.
Example\: HPAuth_4f3b5044e4b05c3dbefdee82
    username - The user name used for URL authentication. For NTLM authentication, the required format is 'domain\user'.
    password - The password used for URL authentication.
    authType - The type of authentication used by this operation when trying to execute the request on the target server.
Valid values\: basic, form, digest, ntlm, kerberos, anonymous (no authentication)
Default value\: anonymous (no authentication used when executing the request)
    timeout - The time to wait for a connection to be established, in  milliseconds. This input needs a value greater than or equal to zero. A  value of '0' represents an infinite timeout.
Default value\: 0
    useCookies - Specifies whether to enable cookie tracking or not. Cookies are stored between consecutive calls. If you specify a non-Boolean value, the default value is used. 
Valid values\: true, false
Default value\: true
    followRedirects - Specifies whether the 'Get' command automatically follows redirects or not. If you specify a non-Boolean value, the default value is used. 
Valid values\: true, false
Default value\: false
    proxy - The proxy server used to access the web site.
    proxyPort - The proxy server port.
    proxyUsername - The proxy server user name.
    proxyPassword - The proxy server password associated with the  input value.
    encodeURL - Specifies whether to encode the URL or not. If you specify a non-Boolean value, the default value is used. 
Valid values\: true, false
Default value\: false
    userAgent - The value to use if the 'USER_AGENT' HTTP header has to be overwritten.
    characterSet - The character encoding to be used for the HTTP 'Get' request and response. 
Default value\: UTF-8
    trustAllRoots - Specifies whether to enable weak security over SSL or not. A SSL certificate is trusted even if no trusted certification authority issued it. 
Valid values\: true, false
Default value\: false
    keystore - The location of the KeyStore file - a URL or the local path to it. This input is empty if no HTTPS client authentication is used. 
Example\: %JAVA_HOME%/jre/lib/security/cacerts
    keystorePassword - The password associated with the KeyStore file.
    trustKeystore - The location of the TrustStore file - a URL or the local path to it. This input is empty if no HTTPS server authentication is used. 
Example\: %JAVA_HOME%/jre/lib/security/cacerts
    trustPassword - The password associated with the TrustStore file.
    kerberosConfFile - The path to the Kerberos configuration file. If this input is empty, the  (Key Distribution Center) and  get their values from the full domain name obtained from the web server URL.
    socketTimeout - The time to wait for data to be retrieved, in milliseconds. This input needs a value greater than or equal to zero. A  value of '0' represents an infinite timeout.
Default value\: 0
    headerNamesList - A list of header names to be used for the request.
Example\: Accept,Content-Type
    headerValuesList - A list of header values to be used for the request. 
Example\: text/plain,application/x-www-form-urlencoded
    queryNamesList - A list of query parameter names to be used for the request. 
Example\: parameterName1,parameterName2 
    queryValuesList - A list of query parameter values to be used for the request. 
Example\: parameterValue1,parameterValue2
    delimiter - The delimiter used to separate list elements.
Default value\: (carriage return)

Results\:
    serverDetails - This is the primary output. A JSON array of objects describing a server. The JSON object contains the name, updated time, created time, tenant ID, access IPs, flavor and image details. It also contains the metadata, addresses and links for the server.

Responses\:
    success - The operation completed as stated in the description.
    failure - The operation completed unsuccessfully.

Note\:
See the 'Library/Operations/HTTP Client/' operations for additional information.
